The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Thursday, May 13, 2004 				 Glimpses from the Tagorean stage
In commemoration of Rabindranath Tagores 143rd birth anniversary, the state governments information and cultural affairs department hosts an exhibition of photographs based on performances of Tagores plays. A one-of-its-kind exhibition, this display of rare photographs carries more than an academic interest. It enables old-timers and lovers of Bengali theatre revive memories of legendary performances of Tagores most popular plays; to some of which the playwright himself lent his histrionic talents. Unforgettable scenes from his most famous plays like Prayaschitta, Bisarjan, Raja O Rani, Malini, Chaar Adhyay, Shesh Raksha, Chirakumar Sabha and Raktakarabi, among others, captured through the lens for posterity, are on show.																								Event: Rabindranath O Bangla Natak  an exhibition of photographs of Tagores plays																								When: Till May 16; 2 pm - 8 pm																								Where: Gaganendra Shilpa Pradarshasala, Calcutta Information Centre
